Title: UFO's: 50 Years of Denial, Expanded

reviewText: There are plenty of UFO documentaries, but this one tells it straight, in good chronological order, gets to the issues, and as such is an indispensible introduction to the subject.  The testimonies of Jesse Marcel and Philip J. Corso are especially compelling because they were military brass who kept their secrecy oaths until near the end of their lives. Former Astronaut and moonwalker Edgar Mitchell is convinced extraterrestrial intelligences are visiting our planetary system.This documentary is a well needed corrective to the debunking propoganda of mainstream media (the Peter Jennings ABC special, for example) that passes for "objective" analysis. Perhaps if PBS or ABC aired this documentary in prime time people might begin to wonder. But that is never going to happen.
Title: UFO's: 50 Years of Denial, Expanded

reviewText: I own probably 10 UFO dvd's - - and this one, by far, is the best of all of them !  The interview with Colonel Philip Corso in the "special bonus material" section was truly superb.  GREAT research went into this marvelous movie.  This DVD won two EBE awards.  From Area 51, to Roswell, to Gerald Ford's memoirs to the never-ending governmental cover-ups, this DVD will hold your interest for the entire 2-hours !  A MUST PURCHASE !!
summary: The best DVD on the subject out there.
Title: UFO's: 50 Years of Denial, Expanded
